                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-03-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Conger acknowledges receipt of Mr. Hay’s telegram of the 12th, and states
                    that the minister for foreign affairs is pleased with the friendly interest
                    manifested by the United States, and says China is resolved to maintain
                    neutrality and that provocation will not be given to either belligerent.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
